<collectionCode id="C0ACAE4E7A36FFFFFDFCF809FDC1F87C" box="[541,626,1968,1992]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">USNM</collectionCode>
. A female 
<typeStatus id="790688297A36FFFFFD11F809FCE2F87C" box="[752,849,1968,1992]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">paratype</typeStatus>
bearing the same locality label as the 
<typeStatus id="790688297A36FFFFFAECF816FADCF87C" box="[1293,1391,1967,1992]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
but with the date of 
<date id="D203104B7A36FFFFFE80F86AFE1DF858" box="[353,430,2003,2028]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">5 May</date>
is deposited in the 
<collectionCode id="C0ACAE4E7A36FFFFFD41F86DFD5BF858" box="[672,744,2004,2028]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34784" name="Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">ANSP</collectionCode>
. The 
<typeStatus id="790688297A36FFFFFCCEF86AFC22F858" box="[815,913,2003,2028]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">holotype</typeStatus>
is a female, not a “ 
<specimenCount id="B0BBFD027A36FFFFFB66F86DFB2EF858" box="[1159,1181,2004,2028]" pageId="14" pageNumber="97" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
?”, as Cresson noted questionably in the original publication (
<bibRefCitation id="C22C4B7A7A37FFFEFD91FF21FCFCFF04" author="Cresson" box="[624,847,151,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98" refString="Cresson, E. T. Jr. (1922) Descriptions of new genera and species of the dipterous family Ephydridae. V. Entomological News, 33 (5), 135 - 137." type="journal article" year="1922">Cresson 1922: 135</bibRefCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus id="790688297A37FFFEFC7CFF21FC4DFF04" box="[925,1022,152,176]" pageId="15" pageNumber="98">paratype</typeStatus>
is a female, although its wings are folded along the sides of the abdomen, partially blocking any view of its abdomen.
</paragraph>
